review_content:
330 ml bottle bought at The magstore on Cameron Road, Tsim Sha Tsui.



Clear golden amber colour; Half finger head with soapy white foam which fades in 30 seconds. Good sticky lacing with fizzy small carbonation;
Quite fragrant aroma of Ale malt, with strong caramel, toffee, butterscotch, light sugar, thin lemon and light grass. Some tropical fruity nose come through as beer warms; Close to light sweet taste of moderate Ale malt, with caramel, toffee, light red fruits, molasses, light biscuits, lemon, liquorices, moderate bitter hops and quite strong grass;
Mid to light body. Slick palate; Mouth Feel is moderate Amber maltyness in a light and strong-carboed background. Strong caramel, toffee and a touch of butterscotch for smoothness. Red fruits and molasses compliments well with good strong lemon to round. Pretty good!... Hoppiness is thin lemon and light grass in nose. Lemon, liquorices, and strong grass in taste; Bitterness is liquorices-like, quite strong for a lasting, mid-to-high astringent sweet malty finish; Fairly dry after taste. Caramel sweet and bitter to mouth.



Comments: This one’s hop flavors is very strong for a Pale Ale, but still the caramel and toffee characters stole the show. Its slightly buttery feel enhances its attractiveness somewhat. Not the most outstanding but certainly enjoyable. Good!
